Japan writes off $ 80 mln debt to Bangladesh . Japan has written off 9 . 14 billion yen ( $ 80 million ) in unpaid debt to Bangladesh , government officials said on Wednesday . The debt relief came after an agreement signed between the two governments in Dhaka on Wednesday . The officials said Tokyo had turned the loan into grant assistance for import of commodities and equipment . But , they said , the agreement made it mandatory that the imports would be from member countries of the Organisation for Economic Cooperation and Development ( OECD ) , of which Japan is a member . Bangladesh is one of the largest beneficiaries of Japanese overseas aid programmes , having received more than $ 5 billion since 1971 , the officials said . 
